President Obama has announced his intent to nominate and appoint several individuals to key Administration posts. The nominations include Bill Baer for Assistant Attorney General for the Antitrust Division, Department of Justice; Marcilynn A. Burke for Assistant Secretary for Land and Minerals Management, Department of the Interior; Joseph Jordan for Administrator for Federal Procurement Policy, Office of Management and Budget; John Norris for Commissioner, Federal Energy Regulatory Commission; and Heidi Shyu for Assistant Secretary of the Army for Acquisition, Logistics, and Technology, Department of Defense. The appointments include Milton Irvin as a Member of the President's Board of Advisors on Historically Black Colleges and Universities and George B. Walker, Jr. as a Member of the President's Board of Advisors on Historically Black Colleges and Universities. President Obama expressed his confidence in these individuals and his excitement to work with them in the future.